ess to the hospitals, birth centers, and care providers that will uphold or facilitate the practice. This chapter will explore First Nations women’s (as the participants featured identified as women) birth stories through poetic inquiry, as they relate to birthing on Country, Indigenous women’s access thereto, and their narratives of interaction with care systems and providers. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2022.},
